'''Ground itch''' refers to the inflammatory reaction resulting from certain [[helminth]]ic invasions into the skin.<ref>[http://www.dermatologyinfo.net/english/chapters/chapter14.htm Principles of Pediatric Dermatology - Chapter14 : SKIN MANIFESTATIONS OF MEDICAL HELMINTHES<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

The responsible agents include:
* Threadworms
**[[Strongyloides stercoralis]]
* Hookworms
** [[Ancylostoma duodenale]]
** [[Necator americanus]]
** [[Ancylostoma braziliense]]

